    • Method Detail

      • render

        public void render()
        Renders the gui, drawing a background. It draws the following elements:
        - a heatmap over the background
        - a title text block
        - a instruction button that toggles to display the keys
        - a button for displaying whether walls kill, toggling the state of walls kill
        - a button to start the game
        Also triggers the buttons to change color if they are being hovered.

      • update

        private void update()
        Calls the update method for every button. Most often used to handle hovering effect of button.

      • mousePressed

        void mousePressed()
        Handles mouse presses and checks if button have been clicked. Initiates following actions:
        - checks instructionsButton
        - checks startGameButton and starts game if it is clicked
        - checks wallsKillButton and updates walls setting.
